-- Mabuchi Says Government Wants Japan Air Turnaround Plan Agreed by November
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r
-- 2010-09-21T07:10:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/government-wants-jal-turnaround-plan-agreed-by-november-mabuchi-says.html
Japanese Transport Minister Sumio
Mabuchi said Japan Airlines Corp., which is restructuring under
bankruptcy protection, should obtain agreement on its turnaround
plan by November.  Mabuchi spoke to reporters today in Tokyo. He also said
Japan will discuss lowering landing fees and that the country is
considering incentives to encourage low-cost carriers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
